Retrieve Sequence Names (Generic Function)

Source: R/AllGenerics.R
ps_seq_names.Rd

`ps_seq_names` is a **generic function** that extracts the sequence names or identifiers from an object containing promoter sequence data.

ps_seq_names(x, ...)

Arguments

x

An object containing sequence information.

...

Additional arguments passed to specific methods.

Value

  • If `x` is a `PSMatrix` object: a **character vector** of sequence names corresponding to the analyzed promoter regions.

  • If `x` belongs to another supported class, the return format may vary.

Details

Methods should be implemented for specific object classes storing sequence data.

Examples

pfm1_path <- system.file("extdata", "pfm1.rds", package = "PscanR")
pfm1 <- readRDS(pfm1_path)
ps_seq_names(pfm1)
